ictionary with the key/value pairs"]}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.get_hit_count", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns hit counts for an object.\n\n- Return total hits for an object:\n{% get_hit_count for [object] %}\n\n- Get total hits for an object as a specified variable:\n{% get_hit_count for [object] as [var] %}\n\n- Get total hits for an object over a certain time period:\n{% get_hit_count for [object] within [\"days=1,minutes=30\"] %}\n\n- Get total hits for an object over a certain time period as a variable:\n{% get_hit_count for [object] within [\"days=1,minutes=30\"] as [var] %}\n\nThe time arguments need to follow datetime.timedelta's limitations:\nAccepts days, seconds, microseconds, milliseconds, minutes,\nhours, and weeks."]}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.insert_hit_count_js_variables", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Injects JavaScript global variables into your template.  These variables\ncan be used in your JavaScript files to send the correctly mapped HitCount\nID to the server (see: hitcount-jquery.js for an example).\n\n{% insert_hit_count_js_variables for [object] %}"]}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.get_hit_count_js_variables", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Injects JavaScript global variables into your template.  These variables\ncan be used in your JavaScript files to send the correctly mapped HitCount\nID to the server (see: hitcount-jquery.js for an example).\n\n{% get_hit_count_js_variables for [object] as [var_name] %}\n\nWill provide two variables:\n    [var_name].pk = the hitcount pk to be sent via JavaScript\n    [var_name].ajax_url = the relative url to post the ajax request to"]}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.insert_hit_count_js", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Injects the JavaScript into your template that works with jquery.postcsrf.js.\n\n{% insert_hit_count_js_variables for [object] %}"]}], "variables": [{"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.register", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.GetHitCount", "bases": ["template.Node"], "methods": [{"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.GetHitCount.handle_token", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.GetHitCount.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj_as_str", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "as_varname", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "period", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.GetHitCount.render", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "context", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.GetHitCount.handle_token", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.WriteHitCountJavascriptVariables", "bases": ["template.Node"], "methods": [{"name": "hitcount.templatetags.hitcount_tags.WriteHitCountJavascriptVaria